All is set for the kick-off of the maiden Oyo Unity Cup on the auspices of the Minister of Youth and Sports Development Sunday Dare. The Cup which will draw participants across the 16 Federal Constituencies the state, the Nigerian Union of Journalists (NUJ) and the Nigerian Youth Service Corps (NYSC) will be launched on Saturday at the Soun Stadium in Ogbomoso, Oyo State. The Minister will lead notable former Nigerian Internationals including Daniel Amokachi, Taribo West and Joseph Yobo to the event billed to interact and inspire young talents. It would be recalled that the Minister had earlier said the aim of the tournament was to promote football at the grassroots level in addition to discovering young talents from the nooks and crannies of Oyo State.